WHAT IS IBM GARAGE?
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

IBM Garage is IBM Consulting's collaborative, value-obsessed engagement model.
It integrates technologies, methods, practices, and human expertise to identify,
track, and realize business value at each stage of enterprise change — rapidly
turning ideas into measurable, meaningful outcomes.

Core philosophy: "startup speed at enterprise scale."

IBM Garage helps de-risk transformation while quickly scaling impact. It aligns
work to the biggest drivers of value, transparently tracks that value as it is
realized in each stage, and scales new ways of working by bringing together:
- Enterprise Design Thinking
- Agile development
- DevSecOps practices
- Generative AI tools from IBM and partners

IBM Garage originated as IBM Cloud Garage in San Francisco in 2014. It now
operates in startup communities globally, with IBM consultants working
side-by-side with client teams in cross-disciplinary squads.

