THE IBM GARAGE METHOD FIELD GUIDE — SEVEN PHASES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The IBM Cloud Garage Method Field Guide documents IBM's approach to enable
business, development, and operations to continuously design, deliver, and
validate new function. Seven phases:

1. CULTURE — Agile mindset, psychological safety, squad structure, T-shaped
   skills, pair programming culture.

2. THINK — Design Thinking, user research, Hills, Playbacks, Sponsor Users,
   hypothesis formation, MVP definition.

3. CODE — Test-Driven Development (TDD), pair programming, continuous integration,
   automated testing, refactoring, reference architectures.

4. DELIVER — CI/CD pipelines, DevSecOps, automated deployment, blue/green
   deployments, feature flags, release management.

5. RUN — Site Reliability Engineering (SRE), monitoring, alerting, incident
   response, chaos engineering, capacity planning.

6. MANAGE — Outcome-based roadmaps, backlog management, risk registers,
   stakeholder communication, metrics and KPIs.

7. LEARN — Sprint retrospectives, metrics analysis, user feedback loops,
   blameless post-mortems, methodology refinement.

