THE SQUAD MODEL
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

IBM Garage works in cross-disciplinary squads with clients working side-by-side
with IBMers. Through this immersive co-creation, IBM enables clients to work
in new ways permanently.

SQUAD LEADER (Change Agent):
- Experienced in lean startup, lean UX, Enterprise Design Thinking, Agile, DevOps
- Ideally a certified Enterprise Design Thinking coach
- Facilitates complex workshops; ensures agile is foundational culture

ARCHITECT:
- Helps the squad focus on sprint goals
- Prevents teams getting lost in details
- Ensures architectural consistency and reference architecture usage

T-SHAPED SKILLS MODEL:
Each squad member should have:
- Depth: Deep expertise in one area (their SME specialty)
- Breadth: Wide enough skills to help others and follow team progress

