KEY PRACTICES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

FAIL FAST, LEARN FAST:
Always focus on which aspects of an idea need testing to determine whether
continued investment is warranted. Occasionally MVPs don't require a technical
solution — the hypothesis is the target, not the software.

FUNNEL AND FIREWALL (Product Management practice):
- FUNNEL: PM gathers requirements from stakeholders through workshops.
  Output: prioritized backlog with KPIs, USPs, value propositions, estimates.
- FIREWALL: PM shields delivery team from interruptions to maintain sprint focus.
  Regular demos to stakeholders enable fast feedback loops.

OUTCOME-BASED ROADMAPS (OBRs):
Connects product vision and business objective with high-level features.
Prevents losing sight of overall objectives in day-to-day execution.

